params._vote: Vote true to fund the ICO. False to get a refund.

castVote(bool).return: Vote(address indexed voter, uint indexed round, uint indexed votingRoundNumber, bool vote)

initialize(address,address,uint256).details: Start allocation one week from now- initialize(0x123.., 0x321, 0x222, current unix time (seconds) + 1 week);

params._allocStartTime: Start of allocation period. Typically a week. Unix time stamp in seconds.
params._escrow: The escrow address. This is a multisig wallet address
params._icoToken: The ICO's ERC20 token. Get the voters from this contract

setupNextRound(uint256,uint256).details: start one week from now with one unit of erc20 funding - setupNextRound(now + 1 week, 1 * 10**stableCoin.decimals());

params._fundSize: Amount of funding attempting to release. This is a big number to web3. There are typically decimal places in ERC20 tokens too.
params._startTime: Start of the voting period. Typically a week before closed. Unix time stamp in seconds. After this time, startRound must be called to start the round.

setupNextRound(uint256,uint256).return: NewRoundInfo(uint indexed round, uint indexed votingRoundNumber, uint startTime, uint endTime, uint fundSize)

userRefund().return: Transfer(address indexed from, address indexed to, uint indexed quantity)

allocVotes().notice: Each user calls this to allocate their votes. Must be in allocation time-period/state (see initialize)

approveNewRound().notice: After round is over, this tallies votes and either refunds users or funds the ICO.

castVote(bool).notice: Each user calls this to vote on ICO funding or get a refund. Must be in InRound state (see setupNextRound)

getHasVoted(address,uint256,uint256).notice: Gets if the user has voted, for given funding-round and voting-round number

getRoundEndTime().notice: Gets the current round end time

getRoundStartTime().notice: Gets the current round start time

getUserRefundSize(address).notice: Gets user's refund size. Assumes they were not refunded yet

getUserVotePower(address).notice: Gets user vote power. Based on square root of vote allocation

initialize(address,address,uint256).notice: Initialize the token poll. This also sets the voter allocation time period.

setupNextRound(uint256,uint256).notice: Sets up the next round to vote on approving ICO funding. Must be in state NextRoundApproved

startRefund_illegalRoundDelay().notice: This starts the refund if there was no funding for too long a time. It only needs to be called once to be put in refund state. Must be in NextRoundApproved state.

startRefund_voteFailed().notice: This starts the refund after a refund was voted for. It only needs to be called once, then the refund starts. Must be in PostRoundDecision state.

startRound().notice: Starts the round. Must be manually called to start the round. (called after round _startTime. see setupNextRound).

userRefund().notice: Each user calls this to get a refund. This happens after users successfully voted to refund. Must be in Refund state.
